1
00:00:05,459 --> 00:00:09,382
What is the actual
original function, purpose

2
00:00:09,382 --> 00:00:12,985
of the senses, 
of sense perception

3
00:00:15,424 --> 00:00:21,046
beyond just navigating
the mundane world?

4
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:24,279
[Bitter Truth Reveals Sweet Absolute]

5
00:00:24,925 --> 00:00:29,244
What really is 
the ultimate purpose of

6
00:00:29,244 --> 00:00:35,011
seeing, hearing, tasting,
touching, smelling, feeling?
 

7
00:00:35,486 --> 00:00:38,501
In the Second Canto of 
the Bhāgavatam

8
00:00:38,501 --> 00:00:42,110
when Śukadev Goswāmī 
begins speaking

9
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:45,773
to Parīkṣit Mahārāj
answering his questions;

10
00:00:45,773 --> 00:00:47,500
there’s a series of verses,

11
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:52,190
five or six verses
that are very heavy,

12
00:00:52,901 --> 00:00:55,406
where he says,

13
00:00:56,053 --> 00:01:00,126
“If the tongue
isn’t used for vibrating

14
00:01:00,126 --> 00:01:02,689
the Holy Name of Kṛṣṇa,
or glorifying Kṛṣṇa,

15
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:05,673
it’s like the croaking of frogs.”

16
00:01:05,673 --> 00:01:07,153
Then it says, 
“Those ears that don’t hear,

17
00:01:07,153 --> 00:01:09,460
are like the earholes of a snake.

18
00:01:09,835 --> 00:01:12,635
The eyes that don’t behold
the divine form of Kṛṣṇa,

19
00:01:12,635 --> 00:01:16,282
are like the eyes on
a peacock plume.”

20
00:01:16,393 --> 00:01:19,772
So, each one of the senses
is denigrated in that way.

21
00:01:19,772 --> 00:01:23,576
And we think, 
this is that sweet boy,

22
00:01:23,576 --> 00:01:26,228
sixteen-year-old boy 
Śukadev Goswāmī,

23
00:01:26,228 --> 00:01:29,959
suddenly saying these
very heavy things.

24
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:31,763
Is he cruel?

25
00:01:31,957 --> 00:01:33,954
Is he mean?

26
00:01:35,607 --> 00:01:39,855
Is it some fanatical 
brahmachārī speaking,

27
00:01:40,222 --> 00:01:45,227
who’s just 
insulting everybody?

28
00:01:47,219 --> 00:01:53,348
Rather we should see 
this as …

29
00:01:54,455 --> 00:01:59,477
it’s brutal, the description,

30
00:01:59,477 --> 00:02:05,606
because of the intensity 
of feeling in the inverse,

31
00:02:05,606 --> 00:02:09,123
that how beautiful is
the form of Kṛṣṇa,

32
00:02:09,123 --> 00:02:12,543
how sweet is the sound
of Kṛṣṇa’s Holy Name,

33
00:02:12,543 --> 00:02:17,571
the sound of the flute,
how soft is the body of Kṛṣṇa,

34
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:22,602
and how extraordinary is
the fragrance, the scent, of Kṛṣṇa.

35
00:02:22,602 --> 00:02:25,067
All of these things
are so wonderful

36
00:02:25,067 --> 00:02:27,636
that someone will say:

37
00:02:27,636 --> 00:02:34,645
“If you’re not using it for that,
you’ve wasted your life.

38
00:02:34,645 --> 00:02:37,661
What are they for?
What are your senses for?

39
00:02:37,675 --> 00:02:41,475
Even in this world we have people
who say things like that.

40
00:02:41,475 --> 00:02:46,064
They’ll say, “Oh, if you haven’t done this,
you haven’t lived!” Right?

41
00:02:46,064 --> 00:02:49,872
It means that it is
a particular level of intensity

42
00:02:49,872 --> 00:02:52,758
of feeling of appreciation. 
 

